abstract: Amid intense political debate, studies have reached drastically different conclusions about a single-payer system’s price tag, cost to families and effect on the health system.
snippet: Amid intense political debate, studies have reached drastically different conclusions about a single-payer system’s price tag, cost to families and effect on the health system.
lead_paragraph: Since Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont drove the idea of “Medicare for all,” or a single-payer health system, to the center of the political debate, few other issues have so divided the Democratic presidential candidates and voters. The result has been a cascade of competing assertions, estimates and statistics about the costs and effects of what would amount to a fundamental overhaul of the size and role of the government and the way Americans receive care.

abstract: Michael Bloomberg may join a 2020 field where some leading candidates are railing against wealth like his. It’s complicated.
snippet: Michael Bloomberg may join a 2020 field where some leading candidates are railing against wealth like his. It’s complicated.
lead_paragraph: There is probably never a bad time to be a billionaire. But this, at least, is an especially complicated one.

headline_main: How Should a Billionaire Behave in Public? A Run for President Is One Option
headline_print_headline: For Very Rich,  A Rocky Path  Paved in Gold

abstract: Mr. Bloomberg has been an outspoken voice on gun control and climate change, but his views on taxes would put him on the conservative end of the Democratic field.
snippet: Mr. Bloomberg has been an outspoken voice on gun control and climate change, but his views on taxes would put him on the conservative end of the Democratic field.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg, the former mayor of New York and a billionaire, is likely to enter the Democratic presidential primary. Here’s a look at where he stands on some of the major issues in the race.

headline_main: Where Michael Bloomberg Stands on the Issues

abstract: A Bloomberg-Trump contest would be one between a maker and a faker.
snippet: A Bloomberg-Trump contest would be one between a maker and a faker.
lead_paragraph: Mike Bloomberg should run for president, for two reasons that ought to be dispositive. First, he would be a very good president, potentially a great one. Second, he stands a much better chance of beating Donald Trump than anyone in the current Democratic field.

headline_main: Polls Showing a Close Race in Battleground States
headline_print_headline: Polls Showing a Close Race in Battleground States

abstract: The former New York City mayor submitted paperwork to enter the presidential primary in Alabama, which has the first filing deadline, indicating he would pursue a risky strategy of skipping all four traditional early-state contests.
snippet: The former New York City mayor submitted paperwork to enter the presidential primary in Alabama, which has the first filing deadline, indicating he would pursue a risky strategy of skipping all four traditional early-state contests.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg disrupted the Democratic presidential field on Friday as he took his first steps into the 2020 race, unnerving supporters of Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and prompting Senators Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders to accuse Mr. Bloomberg of seeking to buy the presidency.

headline_main: DealBook: U.S. and China Could Roll Back Tariffs

abstract: Bill Gates and others warn that higher taxes would lead to lower growth. They have their facts backward.
snippet: Bill Gates and others warn that higher taxes would lead to lower growth. They have their facts backward.
lead_paragraph: When Bill Gates founded Microsoft in 1975, the top marginal tax rate on personal income was 70 percent, tax rates on capital gains and corporate income were significantly higher than at present, and the estate tax was a much more formidable levy. None of that dissuaded Mr. Gates from pouring himself into his business, nor discouraged his investors from pouring in their money.
